==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Trichoptera
<hw>Tri*chop"te*ra</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
fr. Gr. <grk>tri`x</grk>, <grk>tricho`s</grk>, a hair + <?/ wing.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A suborder of Neuroptera usually having the
wings covered with minute hairs. It comprises the caddice flies, and is
considered by some to be a distinct order.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Trichopteran</ent>⟦br⟧
